<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880816-0112 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell Gets Army Work </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MD IBM </CO><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   McDonnell Douglas Helicopter Co., a unit of McDonnell Douglas Corp., won a $19.1 million Army contract for improvements to the AH-64 attack helicopter.    International Business Machines Corp. was given $11.2 million in contracts for Air Force satellite-control gear and for Army computer equipment. </TEXT></DOC>